-- Ukraine to Increase Areas Under Spring Grains by 13.6%, IFX Says
-- B y   D a r y n a   K r a s n o l u t s k a
-- 2011-12-26T16:59:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-26/ukraine-to-increase-areas-under-spring-grains-by-13-6-ifx-says.html
Ukraine will increase the area
growing spring grains by 13.6 percent to 8.8 million hectares in
2012 from a year earlier, the  Interfax-Ukraine   news agency 
reported, citing the  Agriculture Ministry .  The country will raise the amount of corn grown by 18.6
percent to 4.3 million hectares, barley by 10 percent to 2.85
million hectares and spring wheat by 4.6 percent to 300,000
hectares, according to the news agency.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Daryna Krasnolutska in Kiev at 
 dkrasnolutsk@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Balazs Penz at 
 bpenz@bloomberg.net  